    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "training_regime",
        "title": "Training Regime: Warmup, Dropout & Label Smoothing",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- 4000-step warmup then decay\n- label smoothing ε=0.1\n\nVaswani et al. use Adam with a warmup schedule: lr increases linearly for 4000 steps then decays proportionally to step^(-0.5), preventing early instability. Label smoothing (ε=0.1) and dropout (0.1) further regularize the model.",
        "position": {
          "x": 7,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "transformer_applications",
        "title": "Transformer Applications & Legacy",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- BERT, GPT built on Transformer\n- vision and multimodal extensions\n\nThe Transformer (Vaswani et al., 2017) became the backbone of BERT, GPT, T5, and virtually every modern LLM, as well as vision models like ViT. It is arguably the most impactful architecture in the history of deep learning.",
        "position": {
          "x": 11,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
    "quiz": {
      "id": "quiz-stage-3",
      "question": "Which model is directly built on the Transformer architecture? Answer with a number.",
